way, I believe that testing the class inside the native image using `Class.forName(\\\"java.lang.StringBuffer\\\")` should be okay.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing to write tests**\\n\\nI'm planning to write tests and use AssertJ statics. It seems I need to create a test under the package `org_codehaus_groovy.groovy_all`. I've noticed that the class name `UtilsTest` conflicts with `groovyjarjarantlr.Utils`, but as long as I don't import it, I should be fine. Alright, let's get started on writing those tests!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Qy8sy2Dp3vB2f250Go46GxBc|fc_01ec6a018a34a118016a2745c1c19881959ae8604f54e5f7f6", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/UtilsTest.groovy", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_codehaus_groovy.groovy_all\n\nimport groovyjarjarantlr.Utils\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat\n\npublic class UtilsTest {\n    @Test\n    void loadsClassDirectlyWhenContextClassLoaderIsUnavailable() {\n        Thread currentThread = Thread.currentThread()\n        ClassLoader originalLoader = currentThread.contextClassLoader\n        try {\n            currentThread.contextClassLoader = null\n\n            Class loadedClass = Utils.loadClass('java.lang.String')\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass).isSameAs(String.class)\n        } finally {\n            currentThread.contextClassLoader = originalLoader\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void fallsBackToDirectClassLoadingWhenContextClassLoaderCannotLoadClass() {\n        Thread currentThread = Thread.currentThread()\n        ClassLoader originalLoader = currentThread.contextClassLoader\n        try {\n            currentThread.contextClassLoader = new RejectingClassLoader(originalLoader)\n\n            Class loadedClass = Utils.loadClass('java.lang.Integer')\n\n            assertThat(loadedClass).isSameAs(Integer.class)\n        } finally {\n            currentThread.contextClassLoader = originalLoader\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void createsInstanceFromClassName() {\n        Object instance = Utils.createInstanceOf('java.lang.StringBuffer')\n\n        assertThat(instance).isInstanceOf(StringBuffer)\n        assertThat(instance.toString()).isEmpty()\n    }\n\n    private static class RejectingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        RejectingClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent)\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        Class loadClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            throw new ClassNotFoundException(name)\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1829, "output": 1323, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27728, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780958637214, "responseId": "resp_01ec6a018a34a118016a2745add9f881959e73946ccf036f21"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Qy8sy2Dp3vB2f250Go46GxBc|fc_01ec6a018a34a118016a2745c1c19881959ae8604f54e5f7f6", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1986 bytes to tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/UtilsTest.groovy"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780958662618}]}
